From 7264842eb874ae315f9d711d5b25e1119be23eca Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 19:47:37 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] feat(slayzone): per-task pooled profiles (different Google
 login per task)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Each task can browse as a named "identity" — its own cookies / Google login /
1Password — fully isolated from other tasks.

- CreateViewParams gains `profile_key`. The host resolves it via ResolveProfile:
  empty → the shell's default profile (sync); a pooled key → get-or-create the
  `slayzone-<key>` profile (ProfileManager::CreateProfileAsync on first use) +
  a ScopedProfileKeepAlive so it survives. CreateView is split into a resolve
  step + CreateViewOnProfile continuation.
- GetOrCreateTaskBrowser now takes the resolved Profile and is keyed so that a
  task switching identities closes its old Browser and rebuilds on the new
  profile. Per-profile cookie + extension isolation is architectural
  (StoragePartition / ExtensionRegistry).
- OpenExtensionsWindow takes a profile_key too → the management window opens on
  the chosen identity, so Web-Store installs (1Password) land in that profile
  and apply to its task panes.

Verified: two panes on "work"/"personal" get independent cookie jars.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
